article.headline: New Mexico St. 95, Prairie View 76
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. -- Wendell McKines scored 22 points and pulled down 13 rebounds as New Mexico State beat Prairie View A&M 95-76. McKines added six assists for the Aggies. Jonathan Gibson scored 22 points for New Mexico State (7-6), followed by Jahmar Young's 19 points and Hamidu Rahman's 14. Young added four assists while Rahman pulled down eight rebounds in the victory. New Mexico State outscored Prairie View A&M 52-36 in the second half. Michael Griffin scored 19 points to lead the Panthers (5-6). Darnell Hugee scored 14 and Christopher Joseph scored 10 points. New Mexico State took a 26-12 lead before Prairie View A&M got back in it. Two Griffin 3-pointers cut the New Mexico State lead to 35-33 and the Aggies led just 43-40 at the break.
